<plot>Dodge City Sheriff Bat Masterson (George Montgomery) is out to prove that a group of cattlemen have framed Merrick (John Maxwell) for murder because he negotiated a treaty granting the Kiowas a reserve in the grass country that the cattlemen wanted for their own grazing land. Knowing that the tribes will wage war again if Merrick is executed, Masterson begins a search for Clay Bennett (David Bruce) who testified he saw the murder. Joining him in the hunt is Marshal Wyatt Earp (Bruce Cowling) and Doc Holliday (James Griffith), both for different purposes. Although Masterson and Holliday have a long standing feud, the latter is persuaded by Merrick's daughter Amy (Nancy Gates) to help.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?360581</url></doc>
